The paper deals with generative models for image reconstruction and synthesis, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces a novel network architecture that combines techniques from both autoencoders and generative adversarial networks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of progressive growing techniques, which is a common approach in neural networks (cs.NE) and computer graphics (cs.GR).
